abstract: The Times asked the presidential candidates for their views on codifying Roe v. Wade, over-the-counter abortion pills and other policies.
snippet: The Times asked the presidential candidates for their views on codifying Roe v. Wade, over-the-counter abortion pills and other policies.
lead_paragraph: The New York Times asked the Democratic presidential candidates to complete a survey on abortion and contraception. Following are the full responses we received, unedited except for corrected typos and punctuation.

headline_print_headline: ‘Tiburones’ Has a Lot of Snaps and No Bite

abstract: Anxious about the cost of a single-payer health system, more voters now support the idea of a government-run plan that would compete with private insurance.
snippet: Anxious about the cost of a single-payer health system, more voters now support the idea of a government-run plan that would compete with private insurance.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — One after another, voters at a recent campaign event here for former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. expressed utter comfort with the centerpiece of his health care platform: an idea once so controversial that Democrats had to drop it from the Affordable Care Act to get the landmark law passed.

abstract: All summer, she was soaring, slinging buzzy plans and climbing in the polls. It’s not summer anymore.
snippet: All summer, she was soaring, slinging buzzy plans and climbing in the polls. It’s not summer anymore.
lead_paragraph: VINTON, Iowa — Elizabeth Warren motors onstage at her campaign events like she is being chased: arm-pump, arm-pump, mid-jog wave. O.K.! Let’s get this thing going.

abstract: In the absence of a clear front-runner, some lower-polling candidates were able to break through — at least for one news cycle.
snippet: In the absence of a clear front-runner, some lower-polling candidates were able to break through — at least for one news cycle.
lead_paragraph: It was a busy week in the Democratic presidential campaign, with a flood of new policies and, of course, another debate.

abstract: An investigation reveals widespread housing discrimination against blacks and other minorities in New York’s suburbs, more than 50 years after the Fair Housing Act.
snippet: An investigation reveals widespread housing discrimination against blacks and other minorities in New York’s suburbs, more than 50 years after the Fair Housing Act.
lead_paragraph: White Americans have long found comfort believing that racial discrimination is a thing of the past.

abstract: The Boston Symphony’s summer festival in the Berkshires will also feature a new tradition: Wagner led by Andris Nelsons.
snippet: The Boston Symphony’s summer festival in the Berkshires will also feature a new tradition: Wagner led by Andris Nelsons.
lead_paragraph: A small string section’s worth of violin stars will celebrate the centenary of the violinist Isaac Stern. Andris Nelsons will conduct the Boston Symphony Orchestra in the third act of Wagner’s “Tannhäuser.” And Paul Lewis will play the five Beethoven piano concertos.

abstract: In events across Atlanta, Ms. Warren, Bernie Sanders and others described how they would address the concerns and priorities of black voters.
snippet: In events across Atlanta, Ms. Warren, Bernie Sanders and others described how they would address the concerns and priorities of black voters.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — One day after a televised debate featuring significant exchanges about race, Democratic presidential candidates fanned out across this capital of black political power to pitch their message to black voters and send a clear signal: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. should not take support from African-Americans for granted.
